President Trump signed the Right to Try Act into law, fulfilling a promise he made to the American people. The law allows patients with terminal illnesses to access experimental treatments that could potentially save their lives. The Vice President, Mike Pence, thanked members of Congress for their bipartisan efforts to pass the legislation and also recognized the courageous families who have fought for improved access to life-saving medicines. President Trump's commitment to the well-being of American families was highlighted, and he was praised for keeping his promises. The event concluded with a prayer and the introduction of President Trump.